    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-08-09T10:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-08-09T10:00:00-05:00" n="396"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/9261: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Shanghai</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-08-09T23:00:00+08:00"
                            >August 9, 1937—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 9—1:05 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>444. Late this afternoon at Chinese military airdrome at terminus of Hungjao Road
                    about 6 miles from western boundary of the Settlement a sentry of Chinese Peace
                    Preservation Corps challenged an approaching motor car and stated he was fired
                    upon and wounded. Car was stopped by a burst of machine gun fire and a Japanese
                    official passenger is reported killed. Chinese servant of American resident
                    injured by stray bullet. Investigation proceeding. Nanking informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
